Are you spontaneous when it comes to travel? Do you show up without a plan & just go with the flow or do you you have an entire excel sheet full of activities planned?  My biggest travel planning tip would be to leave room for both. For the most part  we showed up to Iceland without a plan. We booked our camper a week ahead of time & had a rough idea of stops we wanted to make along the way. I think balance is important when it comes to planning trips. Leave room for spontaneity but research is important because you could be missing out on some really incredible sights if you have no idea they exist. With a bit of wiggle room  you can pop into a random bar because you hear live music & or hangout with that group of strangers because they invited you to their table to have a drink. These things happened to us in Iceland and our free/nonexistent schedule allowed us the freedom to just go with the flow. At the same time  we had a few â€œmust-dosâ€ that we were sure to make time for. Sometimes weâ€™d ask ourselves if we were spending too much time at one stop or if we should be seeing/doing more but itâ€™s more important to cater your trip your interest & doing what feels right to you. Quality is always more important than quantity.
